comment: /** * Returns a new {@link BatchResequencerConfig} instance using default * values for batchSize (100) and batchTimeout * (1000L). * * @return a default {@link BatchResequencerConfig}. */
code: /** * Returns a new {@link BatchResequencerConfig} instance using default * values for batchSize (100) and batchTimeout * (1000L). * * @return a default {@link BatchResequencerConfig}. */ public static BatchResequencerConfig getDefault() { return new BatchResequencerConfig(). }

comment: /**  * Sets the size of the batch to be re-ordered. The default size is 100.  */
code: /**  * Sets the size of the batch to be re-ordered. The default size is 100.  */ public void setBatchSize(int batchSize) {     this.batchSize = batchSize. }

comment: /**  * Sets the timeout for collecting elements to be re-ordered. The default timeout is 1000 msec.  */
code: /**  * Sets the timeout for collecting elements to be re-ordered. The default timeout is 1000 msec.  */ public void setBatchTimeout(long batchTimeout) {     this.batchTimeout = batchTimeout. }
/**  * Whether to allow duplicates.  */ public void setAllowDuplicates(Boolean allowDuplicates) {     this.allowDuplicates = allowDuplicates. }
/**  * Whether to reverse the ordering.  */ public void setReverse(Boolean reverse) {     this.reverse = reverse. }
/**  * Whether to ignore invalid exchanges  */ public void setIgnoreInvalidExchanges(Boolean ignoreInvalidExchanges) {     this.ignoreInvalidExchanges = ignoreInvalidExchanges. }
